The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, August 01, 2004 				 Graphite to acquire German firm
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, July 31: Graphite India Ltd is set to acquire the assets of Germanys Conradty group. The move speeds up Graphite Indias efforts to position itself as a global player with production bases outside India. 																								Europe is an important market for graphite products, and a local manufacturing base will sharpen Graphites competitive edge over global majors. 																								The buyout is strategic to Graphite Indias plan to grow through both organic and inorganic means to a global stature, synergise its existing businesses, strengthen its customer portfolio in the speciality graphite business and move up the value chain. 																								The manufacturing facilities of Conradty, comprising three divisions of Graphite Electrodes, specialities and coating, are all located in Nuremberg, Germany. 																								The electrodes division, which has an installed capacity of about 16500 MT, makes electrodes for use in electric arc furnace-based steel mills.
